*==================================================================================================
* Staff Bar Recipe App Requirements.tct
*==================================================================================================
Private mobile-first staff reference app for bar recipes, wine information, food information, and allergen filtering

*------------------
* Document Control
*------------------
  - Document Name = Staff Bar Recipe App Requirements
  - Format        = TCT
  - Product Type  = Private staff-facing web app
  - Deployment    = Vercel
  - Main Device   = Mobile
  - Secondary     = Desktop
  - Status        = Draft, pending recipes and detailed menu data

*-----------------
* Product Summary
*-----------------
  - Build a private internal web app for store staff
  - The app is used as a fast reference tool during service and training
  - The app contains bar recipes, red wine notes, food descriptions, and allergen information
  - The app helps staff quickly answer customer questions about drinks, food, wine, and dietary restrictions
  - The app must be optimised for mobile use first
  - The app must also work cleanly on desktop

*--------------
* Target Users
*--------------
  - Store staff
  - Bar staff
  - Floor staff
  - New staff during training
  - Managers or supervisors maintaining menu knowledge

*--------------------
* Access And Privacy
*--------------------
  - The app is not public-facing
  - Only selected staff should be able to access the app
  - The app should not be openly searchable or casually accessible by customers
  - Access control should be simple enough for staff to use on mobile
  - Suitable access options include password protection, staff login, invite-only user accounts, or protected deployment access
  - The selected access method should prioritise low friction for staff and basic privacy for internal store content

*-----------------------
* Primary Content Areas
*-----------------------
  - Bar Recipes
      - Cocktail and drink preparation reference
      - Ingredients, measurements, method, garnish, glassware, and staff notes

  - Wine
      - Red wine descriptions and staff selling notes
      - Style, flavour, body, tannin, dryness, region, and food pairing

  - Food
      - Food descriptions and key ingredients
      - Dietary tags, allergens, and service notes

  - Allergen Filter
      - Staff can select customer restrictions
      - App returns suitable food options
      - App can also hide unsuitable food options

*-----------------------
* Bar Recipe Data Model
*-----------------------
  - Each bar recipe should support the following fields
      - Drink Name
      - Category
      - Ingredients
      - Measurements
      - Preparation Method
      - Glassware
      - Ice
      - Garnish
      - Flavour Profile
      - Difficulty
      - Staff Notes
      - Availability Status

  - Recipe measurement format should be consistent
      - Use ml for liquid measurements
      - Use clear units for dashes, drops, slices, wedges, leaves, and egg white
      - Avoid vague measurements unless the recipe intentionally uses them

  - Recipe method should be written as clear service steps
      - Build
      - Shake
      - Stir
      - Strain
      - Double strain
      - Top
      - Garnish
      - Serve

*-----------------
* Wine Data Model
*-----------------
  - Each wine entry should support the following fields
      - Wine Name
      - Wine Type
      - Varietal
      - Country
      - Region
      - Body
      - Tannin Level
      - Acidity
      - Sweetness Or Dryness
      - Flavour Notes
      - Food Pairing
      - Staff Selling Notes
      - Availability Status

  - Red wine descriptions should be practical for staff
      - Focus on how to explain the wine to customers
      - Use simple tasting language
      - Avoid overly technical wine language unless useful for selling or service

*-----------------
* Food Data Model
*-----------------
  - Each food item should support the following fields
      - Dish Name
      - Category
      - Short Description
      - Key Ingredients
      - Allergen Tags
      - Dietary Tags
      - Gluten Free Status
      - Coeliac Suitability
      - Vegan Status
      - Vegetarian Status
      - Staff Notes
      - Availability Status

  - Food descriptions should help staff explain the dish quickly
  - Allergen and dietary fields should be structured, not only written as free text
  - Structured tags are required so filtering works accurately

*----------------------------
* Allergen And Dietary Model
*----------------------------
  - The app should track common allergens and dietary requirements
  - Required tags include
      - Gluten Free
      - Contains Gluten
      - Coeliac Suitable
      - Not Coeliac Suitable
      - Dairy Free
      - Contains Dairy
      - Nut Free
      - Contains Nuts
      - Vegetarian
      - Vegan
      - Contains Seafood
      - Contains Egg
      - Contains Soy

  - Coeliac suitability must be stricter than general gluten-free status
  - A dish can be gluten free but not coeliac suitable if cross-contamination risk exists
  - Allergen information should be explicit and easy to verify
  - Food items with uncertain allergen status should not be shown as safely suitable

*-----------------
* Filtering Logic
*-----------------
  - Staff should be able to filter food by customer needs
  - The app should support positive filters
      - Show gluten-free options
      - Show coeliac-suitable options
      - Show vegan options
      - Show vegetarian options
      - Show dairy-free options
      - Show nut-free options

  - The app should support exclusion filters
      - Hide dishes containing gluten
      - Hide dishes containing dairy
      - Hide dishes containing nuts
      - Hide dishes containing seafood
      - Hide dishes containing egg
      - Hide dishes containing soy

  - The app should support combined restrictions
      - Gluten free + dairy free
      - Coeliac suitable + vegetarian
      - Vegan + nut free
      - Dairy free + no seafood
      - Any other multi-tag combination

  - Filtering result should show
      - Suitable items
      - Potentially unsuitable items when needed
      - Clear reason why an item is excluded or marked unsafe

*------------------------------
* Mobile-First UX Requirements
*------------------------------
  - The app must be designed for mobile first
  - Staff should be able to use it quickly during service
  - Main actions should be reachable with minimal taps
  - Search should be visible and fast
  - Filter controls should be easy to operate with one hand
  - Text should be readable on phone screens
  - Tap targets should be large enough for quick use
  - Content cards should avoid clutter
  - Important dietary warnings should be visually clear
  - The app should avoid heavy animations that slow down mobile performance
  - The app should work well on iPhone and common Android phones

*-------------------------
* Desktop UX Requirements
*-------------------------
  - Desktop layout should be responsive
  - Desktop should use available width efficiently
  - Content can be displayed in wider cards, grids, or tables
  - Search and filters should remain easy to access
  - Desktop should be useful for managers entering, reviewing, or updating content

*----------------------
* Navigation Structure
*----------------------
  - Main navigation should include
      - Bar
      - Wine
      - Food
      - Allergens
      - Search

  - Mobile navigation should be simple and thumb-friendly
  - Recommended mobile navigation style
      - Bottom tab navigation
      - Sticky search area where appropriate
      - Filter drawer or filter chips for dietary restrictions

  - Desktop navigation can use
      - Sidebar
      - Top navigation
      - Section tabs

*---------------------
* Search Requirements
*---------------------
  - Search should work across all major content types
  - Searchable fields should include
      - Drink name
      - Ingredient
      - Recipe category
      - Wine name
      - Wine varietal
      - Wine region
      - Food name
      - Food ingredient
      - Allergen tag
      - Dietary tag

  - Search should feel instant on mobile
  - Search results should be grouped clearly by content type
  - Search should tolerate simple staff input and partial words

*------------------
* Visual Direction
*------------------
  - Visual style should follow the Angelica reference palette
  - Overall mood should be dark, warm, bar-like, refined, and practical
  - The interface should use a deep espresso brown background with bright orange accent elements
  - Primary text should be clean white for readability
  - Secondary text can use warm off-white or muted beige
  - The design should be clean rather than decorative
  - The app should feel polished but not over-designed
  - The design should support fast reading under service pressure
  - App style should support both dark bar environment readability and normal daylight readability

*-------------------
* Colour Parameters
*-------------------
  - App Background        = #210900
  - Page Background       = #210900
  - Card Background       = #2B0D04
  - Elevated Card         = #351207
  - Primary Accent        = #E15F30
  - Accent Hover          = #F26A36
  - Primary Text          = #F8F8F8
  - Secondary Text        = #E8DED6
  - Muted Text            = #BDAEA6
  - Border / Divider      = #5A2412
  - Button Background     = #E15F30
  - Button Text           = #FFFFFF
  - Link Text             = #F8F8F8
  - Link Underline        = #F8F8F8
  - Warning / Allergen    = #FFB020
  - Danger / Not Suitable = #FF5A3D
  - Success / Suitable    = #73C686
  - Neutral Tag           = #E8DED6

*------------------------------
* Admin And Content Management
*------------------------------
  - The app should allow content to be maintained without rebuilding the whole app manually
  - Admin needs are likely to include
      - Add recipe
      - Edit recipe
      - Add wine
      - Edit wine
      - Add food item
      - Edit food item
      - Update allergen tags
      - Update availability status

  - Admin access should be limited to authorised users
  - General staff users should be able to view and search content
  - General staff users should not accidentally edit official recipe or allergen information

*-------------------------
* Deployment Requirements
*-------------------------
  - Deploy the app on Vercel
  - App should be accessible through a private or restricted link
  - App should support mobile browser use without requiring installation
  - App should be installable as a PWA if technically practical
  - App should load quickly on mobile data and venue Wi-Fi
  - App should avoid exposing private internal content to public indexing

*--------------------------
* Performance Requirements
*--------------------------
  - Mobile load speed should be prioritised
  - Search and filtering should respond quickly
  - App should not require heavy images for normal operation
  - Core content should remain readable on slower mobile connections
  - Data structure should support fast filtering without lag
  - Layout should avoid unnecessary re-rendering or heavy visual effects

*----------------------------
* Data Accuracy Requirements
*----------------------------
  - Recipe information must be consistent and service-ready
  - Wine notes must be understandable for staff and customers
  - Allergen information must be treated carefully
  - Coeliac suitability must be separately tracked from general gluten-free status
  - Unknown allergen status should be treated as unsafe or needs confirmation
  - Staff-facing warnings should be clear where cross-contamination risk exists
  - Dietary filtering should not overclaim safety

*-------------------
* Food Content Draft
*-------------------
  - Food content source = Baja Cantina Central server bullet points and food description sheets
  - Food entries should support short service notes, origin/region, ingredients, description, and allergen/dietary tags
  - Current food data is a draft based on provided staff reference photos
  - Allergen and coeliac fields still require confirmation before production use

