*----------------------------
* Food Allergen Draft Notes
*----------------------------
  - Gluten indicators found in current food data
      - Flour tortilla
      - Beer batter
      - Churros
      - Chocolate tart if pastry base contains gluten

  - Dairy indicators found in current food data
      - Cheese
      - Cream
      - Sour cream
      - Ricotta
      - Queso
      - Burrata
      - Mozzarella
      - Condensed milk
      - Evaporated milk
      - Ranch dressing
      - Chipotle mayo if dairy or egg-based recipe requires confirmation

  - Egg indicators found in current food data
      - Mexican flan
      - Mayo-based sauces may contain egg and require confirmation

  - Seafood indicators found in current food data
      - Tuna tartare
      - Ceviche tostadas
      - Prawn ceviche
      - Prawn fajitas
      - Grilled chipotle king prawns
      - Burrito Gobernadora
      - Baja Fish / Prawn Taco

  - Nut indicators found in current food data
      - Chocolate tart includes nuts praline

  - Coeliac safety cannot be assumed from corn-based items
  - Coeliac suitability requires kitchen cross-contamination confirmation
  - Any item with flour tortilla, beer batter, pastry, or uncertain fryer cross-contact should not be marked coeliac suitable without confirmation

*--------------------
* Drink Content Draft
*--------------------
  - Drink content source = provided wine, cocktail, beer, mezcal, tequila, and dessert drink reference sheets
  - Drink entries should support category, taste profile, region, grape or base spirit, body, acidity, and staff selling notes
  - Current drink data is a draft based on provided staff reference photos
  - Pregnant guest guidance should be handled carefully and should not imply that alcoholic drinks are safe for pregnancy

*----------------------------
* Wine Service Notes Draft
*----------------------------
  - Standard Wine Pour = 150ml
  - Red wines can be described by tannin
  - White and rose wines can usually be described without focusing on tannin
  - High-tannin wines on the current list include both Malbecs and the Azara Carmenere
  - For high-tannin wines, staff should suggest protein-rich foods
  - Example Pairings = Wagyu Rib Eye Tacos, Skirt Steak Fajitas

*----------------------------
* Wine Region Notes Draft
*----------------------------
  - Clare Valley, South Australia
      - Description = Cool inland valley famous for world-class Riesling and elegant aromatic wines with vibrant acidity

  - Marlborough, New Zealand
      - Description = New Zealand's largest wine region, globally known for intensely aromatic, crisp Sauvignon Blanc and fresh fruit-driven whites

  - Valencia, Spain
      - Description = Warm Mediterranean region producing expressive local varieties like Bobal, plus fresh coastal whites and smooth juicy reds

  - Adelaide Hills, South Australia
      - Description = Cool-climate elevated area known for refined high-acidity wines such as Gruner Veltliner, Chardonnay, Sauvignon Blanc, and Pinot Noir

  - South Africa
      - Description = Diverse wine country balancing Old-World structure and New-World fruit, especially known for Chenin Blanc and Cabernet-based reds

  - Margaret River, Western Australia
      - Description = Premium coastal region producing elegant high-quality Chardonnay and Bordeaux-style reds with purity and freshness

  - Yarra Valley, Victoria
      - Description = Cool and misty region known for refined lighter-bodied Pinot Noir, Chardonnay, and sparkling wine

  - Mendoza, Argentina
      - Description = High-altitude Andean vineyards producing powerful ripe Malbec with great colour, structure, and concentration

  - Uco Valley, Argentina
      - Description = Very high-altitude part of Mendoza making some of Argentina's most elegant mineral and complex Malbecs

  - Chile
      - Description = Long narrow wine country between ocean and Andes, known for rich spicy reds like Carmenere and structured Cabernets

